message: citations are often omitted from the lead section of an article per [[WP:WHENNOTCITE]]

The source for the claim that 55% of Tanzania is Muslim is "muslimpopulation.com", which may have an inherent bias. The source they cite for Tanzania is this BBC article: "news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/408334.stm", which states that "Tanzania is a secular country, but almost half the population is Muslim". 55% is over half, so under half would be closer to 45%. I could not find any other sources that Tanzania's Muslim population is anywhere near 55 or even 50%, only 35 and 33.
